-- Kenyan Government Agrees to Raise Police Wages by a Quarter, Daily Reports
-- Sarah McGregor
-- 2010-07-08T05:36:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/kenyan-government-agrees-to-raise-police-wages-by-a-quarter-daily-reports.html

          
          
             Kenya agreed to increase the salaries
of police officers by about a quarter in an effort to improve
morale and help motivate them to fight crime,  Business Daily 
reported, citing Internal Security Minister  George Saitoti .  
 Junior officers will get a 28 percent pay rise while senior
officials will earn 25 percent more, the Nairobi-based newspaper
said, without giving the salary amounts.  
 The East African nationâ€™s government also plans to provide
police with more equipment, including 1,000 new vehicles,
closed-circuit television cameras and a forensic laboratory in
the capital Nairobi, Business Daily said.  
